            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... as much as the Bodhisattva makes grow the excellent deeds of three sorts, the mind</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Sooft ein Bodhisattva die dreifach ausgezeichneten Taten fördert.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Every time a Bodhisattva promotes the three times excellent deeds.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>470</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he will abandon the happiness at every occasion; he will make disappear the evil [things that are] the hatred [and] the hostility. [11.] As much as the virtues are growing for him ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... After having made a reflection on the ten states [Skt. bhūmi-] which belong to the Bodhisattvas here, the Bodhisattvas are going (the noble path)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... By paying homage to the Buddhalords (of the past) they are indefatigable for the good of the beings. [12.] ... the encounter with a good friend</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... by doing (good) deeds, by not abandoning the whole world. Even the entering (into) the Perfection completely [and] totally</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">.. by understanding the deceits of the Saṃsāra. [13.] After having accomplished these ten excellent states [Skt. bhūmi-], the B(odhisattva) </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... pertaining to the Buddhalord. And if he is also compassionate through wisdom, (with) constant (wish ?) of the mind </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [14.] He does not obtain anymore any pleasure in this happiness of the Saṃsāra, not even for a single moment. ... compassionate</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... He should not desire the deceits of the Saṃsāra through accurate wisdom. Then he should not be able to ... the afflictions (pertaining to passion)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [15.] While being [sullied] with dirt, he should not then be able to bring the virtues to the brim. He should not be able to trust the beings. If</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the empty impermanence completely without self. Because of the instances of sufferings this one makes himself to feel an aversion [to the world].</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [16.] He firmly seized ... but he was not released. For this reason indeed the Bodhisattva will be attached to the practice [Skt. yoga-] related to emptiness.</seg></seg></choice></p>
